"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The DBSCAN implementation in scikit-learn expects a distance metric to be a callable that takes two 1D arrays as input, but the provided `get_point_distance` function takes two `Point` objects instead. This will lead to a TypeError when DBSCAN tries to call the distance function with the wrong argument types.\",\n  \"patch\": \"28c28\\n< clustering = DBSCAN(metric=get_point_distance).fit(np.array([point.to_list() for point in points]))\\n---\\n> clustering = DBSCAN(metric=lambda x, y: get_point_distance(Point(*x), Point(*y))).fit(np.array([point.to_list() for point in points]))\"\n}"